## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="9bdad-106">Essa classe fornece uma interface para o instalador padrão installUtil no .NET framework.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9bdad-106">This class provides an interface for the standard installUtil installer in the .NET framework.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9bdad-107">Qualquer assembly que contém as classes de automação deve incluir uma classe que é derivada deste tipo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9bdad-107">Any assembly that contains Automation classes should include a class that is derived from this type.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9bdad-108">Isso irá fornecer código que gera o esquema dos objetos de automação, instala-o para a WMI e cria o código de registro do provedor necessário.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9bdad-108">This will provide code that generates the schema of the automation objects, installs it into WMI, and creates the necessary provider registration code.</span></span>  



## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="9bdad-109">O exemplo a seguir mostra como derivar uma classe a partir de <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.DefaultManagementInstaller> classe para instalar um provedor WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9bdad-109">The following example shows how to derive a class from the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.DefaultManagementInstaller> class to install a WMI provider.</span></span>  

```csharp  
// This is the installer class that installs an instrumented assembly.  
// To use the default project installer, simply derive a class from  
// DefaultManagementInstaller.  No methods need to be overridden.  
[System.ComponentModel.RunInstaller(true)]  
public class TheInstaller : DefaultManagementInstaller  
{ }  
```
